obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (2959)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201001_1517807327712&sectionId=2959&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201001_1517807327712
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Legal Metrology Act,`
  line 2009.
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the whole of India.`
  line
  line `(3) It shall come into force on such date^1 as the Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, appoint and different dates may be appointed for different provisions of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. 1st March, 2011, vide notification No. S.O. 1(E), dated 31st December, 2010, see Gazette of India, Extraordinary,`
  line `Part II, Sec. 3(ii).`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (2960)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201001_1517807327712&sectionId=2960&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201001_1517807327712
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line `(a) "Controller" means the Controller of Legal Metrology appointed under section 14;`
  line
  line `(b) "dealer", in relation to any weight or measure, means a person who, carries on, directly or`
  line `otherwise, the business of buying, selling, supplying or distributing any such weight or measure,`
  line `whether for cash or for deferred payment or for commission, remuneration or other valuable`
  line `consideration, and includes a commission agent, an importer, a manufacturer, who sells, supplies,`
  line `distributes or otherwise delivers any weight or measure manufactured by him to any person other than`
  line `a dealer;`
  line
  line `(c) "Director" means the Director of Legal Metrology appointed under section 13;`
  line
  line `(d) "export" with its grammatical variations and cognate expressions, means taking out of India to`
  line `a place outside India;`
  line
  line `(e) "import" with its grammatical variations and cognate expressions, means bringing into India`
  line `from a place outside India;`
  line
  line `(f) "label" means any written, marked, stamped, printed or graphic matter affixed to, or appearing`
  line `upon any pre-packaged commodity;`
  line
  line `(g) "Legal Metrology" means that part of metrology which treats units of weighment and`
  line `measurement, methods of weighment and measurement and weighing and measuring instruments, in`
  line `relation to the mandatory technical and legal requirements which have the object of ensuring public`
  line `guarantee from the point of view of security and accuracy of the weighments and measurements;`
  line
  line `(h) "legal metrology officer" means Additional Director, Additional Controller, Joint Director,`
  line `Joint Controller, Deputy Director, Deputy Controller, Assistant Director, Assistant Controller and`
  line `Inspector appointed under sections 13 and 14;`
  line
  line `(i) "manufacturer" in relation to any weight or measure, means a person who--`
  line
  line `(i) manufactures weight or measure,`
  line
  line `(ii) manufactures one or more parts, and acquires other parts, of such weight or measure and,`
  line `after assembling those parts, claims the end product to be a weight or measure manufactured by`
  line `himself or itself, as the case may be,`
  line
  line `(iii) does not manufacture any part of such weight or measure but assembles parts thereof`
  line `manufactured by others and claims the end product to be a weight or measure manufactured by`
  line `himself or itself, as the case may be,`
  line
  line `(iv) puts, or causes to be put, his own mark on any complete weight or measure made or`
  line `manufactured by any other person and claims such product to be a weight or measure made or`
  line `manufactured by himself or itself, as the case may be;`
  line
  line `(j) "notification" means a notification published in the Official Gazette;`
  line
  line `(k) "protection" means the utilisation of reading obtained from any weight or measure, for the`
  line `purpose of determining any step which is required to be taken to safeguard the well-being of any`
  line `human being or animal, or to protect any commodity, vegetation or thing, whether individually or`
  line collectively;
  line
  line `(l) "pre-packaged commodity" means a commodity which without the purchaser being present is`
  line `placed in a package of whatever nature, whether sealed or not, so that the product contained therein`
  line `has a pre-determined quantity;`
  line
  line `(m) "person" includes,--`
  line
  line `(i) a Hindu undivided family,`
  line
  line `(ii) every department or office,`
  line
  line `(iii) every organisation established or constituted by Government,`
  line
  line `(iv) every local authority within the territory of India,`
  line
  line `(v) a company, firm and association of individuals,`
  line
  line `(vi) trust constituted under an Act,`
  line
  line `(vii) every co-operative society, constituted under an Act,`
  line
  line `(viii) every other society registered under the Societies Registration Act, 1860 (21 of 1860);`
  line
  line `(n) "premises" includes--`
  line
  line `(i) a place where any business, industry, production or transaction is carried on by a person,`
  line `whether by himself or through an agent, by whatever name called, including the person who`
  line `carries on the business in such premises,`
  line
  line `(ii) a warehouse, godown or other place where any weight or measure or other goods are`
  line `stored or exhibited,`
  line
  line `(iii) a place where any books of account or other documents pertaining to any trade or`
  line `transaction are kept,`
  line
  line `(iv) a dwelling house, if any part thereof is used for the purpose of carrying on any business,`
  line `industry, production or trade,`
  line
  line `(v) a vehicle or vessel or any other mobile device, with the help of which any transaction or`
  line `business is carried on;`
  line
  line `(o) "prescribed" means prescribed by rules made under this Act;`
  line
  line `(p) "repairer'' means a person who repairs a weight or measure and includes a person who adjusts,`
  line `cleans, lubricates or paints any weight or measure or renders any other service to such weight or`
  line `measure to ensure that such weight or measure conforms to the standards established by or under this`
  line Act;
  line
  line `(q) "State Government", in relation to a Union territory, means the Administrator thereof;`
  line
  line `(r) "sale", with its grammatical variations and cognate expressions, means transfer of property in`
  line `any weight, measure or other goods by one person to another for cash or for deferred payment or for`
  line `any other valuable consideration and includes a transfer of any weight, measure or other goods on the hire-purchase system or any other system of payment by instalments, but does not include a mortgage`
  line `or hypothecation of, or a charge or pledge on, such weight, measure or other goods;`
  line
  line `(s) "seal" means a device or process by which a stamp is made, and includes any wire or other`
  line `accessory which is used for ensuring the integrity of any stamp;`
  line
  line `(t) "stamp" means a mark, made by impressing, casting, engraving, etching, branding, affixing`
  line `pre-stressed paper seal or any other process in relation to, any weight or measure with a view to--`
  line
  line `(i) certifying that such weight or measure conforms to the standard specified by or under this`
  line `Act, or`
  line
  line `(ii) indicating that any mark which was previously made thereon certifying that such weight`
  line `or measure conforms to the standards specified by or under this Act, has been obliterated;`
  line
  line `(u) "transaction" means,--`
  line
  line `(i) any contract, whether for sale, purchase, exchange or any other purpose, or`
  line
  line `(ii) any assessment of royalty, toll, duty or other dues, or`
  line
  line `(iii) the assessment of any work done, wages due or services rendered;`
  line
  line `(v) "verification", with its grammatical variations and cognate expressions, includes, in relation to`
  line `any weight or measure, the process of comparing, checking, testing or adjusting such weight or`
  line `measure with a view to ensuring that such weight or measure conforms to the standards established`
  line `by or under this Act and also includes re-verification and calibration;`
  line
  line `(w) "weight or measure" means a weight or measure specified by or under this Act and includes a`
  line `weighing or measuring instrument.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (2961)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Provisions of this Act to override provisions of any other law.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201001_1517807327712&sectionId=2961&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201001_1517807327712
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `The provisions of this Act shall have effect notwithstanding anything inconsistent therewith contained in any enactment other than this`
  line `Act or in any instrument having effect by virtue of any enactment other than this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (2962)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Units of weights and measures to be based on metric system.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201001_1517807327712&sectionId=2962&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201001_1517807327712
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `Every unit of weight or measure`
  line `shall be in accordance with the metric system based on the international system of units.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (2963)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Base unit of weights and measures.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201001_1517807327712&sectionId=2963&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201001_1517807327712
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `(1) The base unit of--`
  line
  line `(i) length shall be the metre;`
  line
  line `(ii) mass shall be the kilogram;`
  line
  line `(iii) time shall be the second;`
  line
  line `(iv) electric current shall be the ampere;`
  line
  line `(v) thermodynamic temperature shall be the kelvin;`
  line
  line `(vi) luminous intensity shall be the candela; and`
  line
  line `(vii) amount of substance shall be the mole.`
  line
  line `(2) The specifications of the base units mentioned in sub-section (1), derived units and other units shall be such as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (2964)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Base unit of numeration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201001_1517807327712&sectionId=2964&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201001_1517807327712
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `(1) The base unit of numeration shall be the unit of the international`
  line `form of Indian numerals.`
  line
  line `(2) Every numeration shall be made in accordance with the decimal system.`
  line
  line `(3) The decimal multiples and sub-multiples of the numerals shall be of such denominations and be`
  line `written in such manner as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (2965)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Standard units of weights and measures.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201001_1517807327712&sectionId=2965&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201001_1517807327712
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `(1) The base units of weights and measures specified`
  line `in section 5 shall be the standard units of weights and measures.`
  line
  line `(2) The base unit of numeration specified in section 6 shall be the standard unit of numeration.`
  line
  line `(3) For the purpose of deriving the value of base, derived and other units mentioned in section 5, the`
  line `Central Government shall prepare or cause to be prepared objects or equipments in such manner as may`
  line `be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(4) The physical characteristics, configuration, constructional details, materials, equipments,`
  line `performance, tolerances, period of re-verification, methods or procedures of tests shall be such as may be`
  line prescribed.
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (2966)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Standard weight, measures or numeral.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201001_1517807327712&sectionId=2966&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201001_1517807327712
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any weight or measure which conforms to the`
  line `standard unit of such weight or measure and also conforms to such of the provisions of section 7 as are`
  line `applicable to it shall be the standard weight or measure.`
  line
  line `(2) Any numeral which conforms to the provisions of section 6 shall be the standard numeral.`
  line
  line `(3) No weight, measure or numeral, other than the standard weight, measure or numeral, shall be used`
  line `as a standard weight, measure or numeral.`
  line
  line `(4) No weight or measure, shall be manufactured or imported unless it conforms to the standards of`
  line `weight or measure specified under section 8:`
  line
  line `Provided that provisions of this section shall not apply for manufacture done exclusively for export or`
  line `for the purpose of any scientific investigation or research.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (2967)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Reference, secondary and working standard.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201001_1517807327712&sectionId=2967&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201001_1517807327712
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `(1) The reference standards, secondary standards`
  line `and working standards of weights and measures shall be such as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) Every reference standard, secondary standard and working standard shall be verified and stamped`
  line `in such manner and after payment of such fee as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) Every reference standard, secondary standard and working standard which is not verified and`
  line `stamped in accordance with the provisions of sub-section (2) shall not be deemed to be a valid standard.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (2968)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Use of weight or measure for particular purposes.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201001_1517807327712&sectionId=2968&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201001_1517807327712
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `Any transaction, dealing or contract in`
  line `respect of any goods, class of goods or undertakings shall be made by such weight, measure or number as`
  line `may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (2969)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Prohibition of quotation, etc., otherwise than in terms of standard units of weight, measure or numeration.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201001_1517807327712&sectionId=2969&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201001_1517807327712
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `(1) No person shall, in relation to any goods, things or service,--`
  line
  line `(a) quote, or make announcement of, whether by word of mouth or otherwise, any price or`
  line `charge, or`
  line
  line `(b) issue or exhibit any price list, invoice, cash memo or other document, or`
  line
  line `(c) prepare or publish any advertisement, poster or other document, or`
  line
  line `(d) indicate the net quantity of a pre-packaged commodity, or`
  line
  line `(e) express in relation to any transaction or protection, any quantity or dimension, otherwise than`
  line `in accordance with the standard unit of weight, measure or numeration.`
  line
  line `(2) The provisions of sub-section (1) shall not be applicable for export of any goods, things or service.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (2970)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Any custom, usage, etc., contrary to standard weight, measure or numeration to be void.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201001_1517807327712&sectionId=2970&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201001_1517807327712
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `Any custom, usage, practice or method of whatever nature which permits a person to demand, receive or`
  line `cause to be demanded or received, any quantity of article, thing or service in excess of or less than, the`
  line `quantity specified by weight, measure or number in the contract or other agreement in relation to the said`
  line `article, thing or service, shall be void.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (2971)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Appointment of Director, legal metrology officers and other employees.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201001_1517807327712&sectionId=2971&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201001_1517807327712
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central`
  line `Government may, by notification, appoint a Director of legal metrology, Additional Director, Joint`
  line `Director, Deputy Director, Assistant Director and other employees for exercising the powers and`
  line `discharging the duties conferred or imposed on them by or under this Act in relation to inter-State trade`
  line `and commerce.`
  line
  line `(2) The qualifications of the Director and legal metrology officers appointed under sub-section (1) shall be such as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) The Director and every legal metrology officer, appointed under sub-section (1), shall exercise`
  line `such powers and discharge such functions in respect of such local limits as the Central Government may,`
  line `by notification, specify.`
  line
  line `(4) Every legal metrology officer appointed under sub-section (1) shall exercise powers and discharge`
  line `duties under the general superintendence, direction and control of the Director.`
  line
  line `(5) The Director, the Controller and every legal metrology officer authorised to perform any duty by`
  line `or under this Act shall be deemed to be a public servant within the meaning of section 21 of the Indian`
  line `Penal Code (45 of 1860).`
  line
  line `(6) No suit, prosecution or other legal proceeding shall lie against the Director, the Controller and legal metrology officer authorised to perform any duty by or under this Act in respect of anything which`
  line `is in good faith done or intended to be done under this Act or any rule or order made thereunder.`
  line
  line `(7) The Central Government may, with the consent of the State Government and subject to such`
  line `conditions, limitations and restrictions as it may specify in this behalf, delegate such of the powers of the`
  line `Director under this Act as it may think fit to the Controller of legal metrology in the State, and such`
  line `Controller may, if he is of opinion that it is necessary or expedient in the public interest so to do, delegate`
  line `such of the powers delegated to him as he may think fit to any legal metrology officer and where any such`
  line `delegation of powers is made by such Controller, the person to whom such powers are delegated shall`
  line `exercise those powers in the same manner and with the same effect as if they had been conferred on him`
  line `directly by this Act and not by way of delegation.`
  line
  line `(8) Where any delegation of powers is made under sub-section (7), the powers so delegated shall be`
  line `exercised under the general superintendence, direction and guidance of the Director.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (2972)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Appointment of Controller, legal metrology officers and other employees.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201001_1517807327712&sectionId=2972&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201001_1517807327712
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State`
  line `Government may, by notification, appoint a Controller of legal metrology, Additional Controller, Joint`
  line `Controller, Deputy Controller, Assistant Controller, Inspector and other employees for the State for`
  line `exercising the powers and discharging the duties conferred or imposed on them by or under this Act in`
  line `relation to intra State trade and commerce.`
  line
  line `(2) The qualifications of the Controller and legal metrology officers appointed under sub-section (1)`
  line `shall be such as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) The Controller and every legal metrology officer, appointed under sub-section (1), shall exercise`
  line `such powers and discharge such functions in respect of such local limits as the State Government may, by`
  line `notification, specify.`
  line
  line `(4) Every legal metrology officer appointed under sub-section (1) shall exercise and discharge the`
  line `duties under the general superintendence, direction and control of the Controller.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (2973)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `Power of inspection, seizure, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201001_1517807327712&sectionId=2973&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201001_1517807327712
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Director, Controller or any legal metrology officer`
  line `may, if he has any reason to believe, whether from any information given to him by any person and taken`
  line `down in writing or from personal knowledge or otherwise, that any weight or measure or other goods in`
  line `relation to which any trade and commerce has taken place or is intended to take place and in respect of which an offence punishable under this Act appears to have been, or is likely to be, committed are either`
  line `kept or concealed in any premises or are in the course of transportation,--`
  line
  line `(a) enter at any reasonable time into any such premises and search for and inspect any weight,`
  line `measure or other goods in relation to which trade and commerce has taken place, or is intended to`
  line `take place and any record, register or other document relating thereto;`
  line
  line `(b) seize any weight, measure or other goods and any record, register or other document or article`
  line `which he has reason to believe may furnish evidence indicating that an offence punishable under this`
  line `Act has been, or is likely to be, committed in the course of, or in relation to, any trade and commerce.`
  line
  line `(2) The Director, Controller or any legal metrology officer may also require the production of every`
  line `document or other record relating to the weight or measure referred to in sub-section (1) and the person`
  line `having the custody of such weight or measure shall comply with such requisition.`
  line
  line `(3) Where any goods seized under sub-section (1) are subject to speedy or natural decay, the Director,`
  line `Controller or legal metrology officer may dispose of such goods in such manner as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(4) Every search or seizure made under this section shall be carried out in accordance with the`
  line `provisions of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974), relating to searches and seizures.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (2974)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title Forfeiture.
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201001_1517807327712&sectionId=2974&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201001_1517807327712
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every non-standard or unverified weight or measure, and every package made in`
  line `contravention of section 18, used in the course of, or in relation to, any trade and commerce and seized`
  line `under section 15, shall be liable to be forfeited to the State Government:`
  line
  line `Provided that such unverified weight or measure shall not be forfeited to the State Government if the`
  line `person from whom such weight or measure was seized gets the same verified and stamped within such`
  line `time as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) Every weight, measure or other goods seized under section 15 but not forfeited under`
  line `sub-section (1), shall be disposed of by such authority and in such manner as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (2975)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 17
  title `Manufacturers, etc., to maintain records and registers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201001_1517807327712&sectionId=2975&sectionno=17&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201001_1517807327712
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every manufacturer, repairer or`
  line `dealer of weight or measure shall maintain such records and registers as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) The records and registers maintained under sub-section (1) shall be produced at the time of`
  line `inspection to the persons authorised for the said purpose under sub-section (1) of section 15.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (2976)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 18
  title `Declarations on prepackaged commodities.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201001_1517807327712&sectionId=2976&sectionno=18&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201001_1517807327712
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `(1) No person shall manufacture, pack, sell,`
  line `import, distribute, deliver, offer, expose or possess for sale any pre-packaged commodity unless such package is in such standard quantities or number and bears thereon such declarations and particulars in such manner as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) Any advertisement mentioning the retail sale price of a pre-packaged commodity shall contain a`
  line `declaration as to the net quantity or number of the commodity contained in the package in such form and`
  line `manner as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (2977)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 19
  title `Registration for importer of weight or measure.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201001_1517807327712&sectionId=2977&sectionno=19&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201001_1517807327712
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `No person shall import any weight or`
  line `measure unless he is registered with the Director in such manner and on payment of such fees, as may be`
  line prescribed.
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (2978)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 20
  title `Non-standard weights and measures not to be imported.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201001_1517807327712&sectionId=2978&sectionno=20&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201001_1517807327712
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `No weight or measure, whether`
  line `singly or as a part or component of any machine shall be imported unless it conforms to the standards of`
  line `weight or measure established by or under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (2979)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 21
  title `Training in Legal Metrology.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201001_1517807327712&sectionId=2979&sectionno=21&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201001_1517807327712
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `(1) For imparting training in Legal Metrology and other allied`
  line `branches of knowledge the "Indian Institute of Legal Metrology" (hereinafter referred to as the`
  line `"Institute") established under the provisions of the Standards of Weights and Measures Act, 1976`
  line `(60 of 1976), shall be deemed to have been established under the corresponding provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) The management and control of the Institute, the teaching staff and other employees, the courses`
  line `and curricula for training thereat, the qualifications, which a person shall possess in order to be eligible`
  line `for admission thereto shall be such as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (2980)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 22
  title `Approval of model.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201001_1517807327712&sectionId=2980&sectionno=22&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201001_1517807327712
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `Every person, before manufacturing or importing any weight or measure`
  line `shall seek the approval of model of such weight or measure in such manner, on payment of such fee and`
  line `from such authority as may be prescribed:`
  line
  line `Provided that such approval of model may not be required in respect of any cast iron, brass, bullion,`
  line `or carat weight or any beam scale, length measures (not being measuring tapes) which are ordinarily used`
  line `in retail trade for measuring textiles or timber, capacity measures, not exceeding twenty litre in capacity,`
  line `which are ordinarily used in retail trade for measuring kerosene, milk or potable liquors:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the prescribed authority may, if he is satisfied that the model of any weight or`
  line `measure which has been approved in a country outside India conforms to the standards established by or`
  line `under this Act, approve such model without any test or after such test as he may deem fit.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (2981)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 23
  title `Prohibition on manufacture, repair or sale of weight or measure without licence.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201001_1517807327712&sectionId=2981&sectionno=23&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201001_1517807327712
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `(1) No`
  line `person shall manufacture, repair or sell, or offer, expose or possess for repair or sale, any weight or`
  line `measure unless he holds a licence issued by the Controller under sub-section (2):`
  line
  line `Provided that no licence to repair shall be required by a manufacturer for repair of his own weight or`
  line `measure in a State other than the State of manufacture of the same.`
  line
  line `(2) For the purpose of sub-section (1), the Controller shall issue a licence in such form and manner,`
  line `on such conditions, for such period and such area of jurisdiction and on payment of such fee as may be`
  line prescribed.
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (2982)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 24
  title `Verification and stamping of weight or measure.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201001_1517807327712&sectionId=2982&sectionno=24&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201001_1517807327712
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every person having any weight or`
  line `measure in his possession, custody or control in circumstances indicating that such weight or measure is`
  line `being, or is intended or is likely to be, used by him in any transaction or for protection, shall, before`
  line `putting such weight or measure into such use, have such weight or measure verified at such place and`
  line `during such hours as the Controller may, by general or special order, specify in this behalf, on payment of`
  line `such fees as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government may prescribe the kinds of weights and measures for which the`
  line `verification is to be done through the Government approved Test Centre.`
  line
  line `(3) The Government approved Test Centre shall be notified by the Central Government or the State`
  line `Government, as the case may be, in such manner, on such terms and conditions and on payment of such`
  line `fee as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(4) The Government approved Test Centre shall appoint or engage persons having such qualifications`
  line `and experience and collect such fee on such terms and conditions for the verification of weights and`
  line `measures specified under sub-section (2) as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (2983)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 25
  title `Penalty for use of non-standard weight or measure.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 18 of 2023, s. 2 and the Schedule, for certain words (w.e.f. 1-10-2023).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201001_1517807327712&sectionId=2983&sectionno=25&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201001_1517807327712
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `Whoever uses or keeps for use any`
  line `weight or measure or makes use of any numeration otherwise than in accordance with the standards of`
  line `weight or measure or the standard of numeration, as the case may be, specified by or under this Act, shall`
  line `be punished with fine which may extend to ^1[one lakh rupees and for the second offence with fine which`
  line `may extend to two lakh rupees and for the third and subsequent offence, with fine which may extend to`
  line `five lakh rupees].`
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (2984)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 26
  title `Penalty for alteration of weight and measure.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201001_1517807327712&sectionId=2984&sectionno=26&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201001_1517807327712
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `Whoever tampers with, or alters in any way,`
  line `any reference standard, secondary standard or working standard or increases or decreases or alters any`
  line `weight or measure with a view to deceiving any person or knowing or having reason to believe that any`
  line `person is likely to be deceived thereby, except where such alteration is made for the correction of any`
  line `error noticed therein on verification, shall be punished with fine which may extend to fifty thousand`
  line `rupees and for the second and subsequent offence with imprisonment for a term which shall not be less`
  line `than six months but which may extend to one year or with fine or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (2985)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 27
  title `Penalty for manufacture or sale of non-standard weight or measure.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201001_1517807327712&sectionId=2985&sectionno=27&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201001_1517807327712
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `Every person who`
  line `manufactures or causes to be manufactured or sells or offers, exposes or possesses for sale, any weight or`
  line `measure which,--`
  line
  line `(a) does not conform to the standards of weight or measure specified by or under this Act; or`
  line
  line `(b) which bears thereon any inscription of weight, measure or number which does not conform to`
  line `the standards of weight, measure or numeration specified by or under this Act, except where he is`
  line `permitted to do so under this Act, shall be punished with a fine which may extend to twenty thousand`
  line `rupees and for the second or subsequent offence with imprisonment for a term which may extend to`
  line `three years or with fine or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (2986)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 28
  title `Penalty for making any transaction, deal or contract in contravention of the prescribed standards.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 18 of 2023, s. 2 and the Schedule for certain words (w.e.f. 1-10-2023).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201001_1517807327712&sectionId=2986&sectionno=28&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201001_1517807327712
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `Whoever makes any transaction, deal or contract in contravention of the standards of`
  line `weights and measures specified under section 10 shall be punished with fine which may extend to ^1[fifty`
  line `thousand rupees and for the second offence with fine which may extend to one lakh rupees and for the`
  line `third and subsequent offence with fine which may extend to two lakh rupees].`
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (2987)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 29
  title `Penalty for quoting or publishing, etc., of non-standard units.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201001_1517807327712&sectionId=2987&sectionno=29&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201001_1517807327712
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `Whoever violates section 11`
  line `shall be punished with fine which may extend to ten thousand rupees and, for the second or subsequent`
  line `offence, with imprisonment for a term which may extend to one year, or with fine, or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (2988)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 30
  title `Penalty for transactions in contravention of standard weight or measure.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201001_1517807327712&sectionId=2988&sectionno=30&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201001_1517807327712
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line Whoever--
  line
  line `(a) in selling any article or thing by weight, measure or number, delivers or causes to be delivered`
  line `to the purchaser any quantity or number of that article or thing less than the quantity or number`
  line `contracted for or paid for; or`
  line
  line `(b) in rendering any service by weight, measure or number, renders that service less than the`
  line `service contracted for or paid for; or`
  line
  line `(c) in buying any article or thing by weight, measure or number, fraudulently receives, or causes`
  line `to be received any quantity or number of that article or thing in excess of the quantity or number`
  line `contracted for or paid for; or`
  line
  line `(d) in obtaining any service by weight, measure or number, obtains that service in excess of the`
  line `service contracted for or paid for,`
  line
  line `shall be punished with fine which may extend to ten thousand rupees, and, for the second or subsequent`
  line `offence, with imprisonment for a term which may extend to one year, or with fine, or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (2989)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 31
  title `Penalty for non-production of documents, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 18 of 2023, s. 2 and the Schedule for certain words (w.e.f. 1-10-2023).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201001_1517807327712&sectionId=2989&sectionno=31&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201001_1517807327712
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `Whoever, being required by or under this Act`
  line `or the rules made thereunder to submit returns, maintain any record or register, or being required by the`
  line `Director or the Controller or any legal metrology officer to produce before him for inspection any weight`
  line `or measure or any document, register or other record relating thereto, omits or fails without any`
  line `reasonable excuse, so to do, shall be punished with fine which may extend to ^1[twenty-five thousand`
  line `rupees and for the second offence with fine which may extend to fifty thousand rupees and for the third`
  line `and subsequent offence, with fine which may extend to one lakh rupees].`
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (2990)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 32
  title `Penalty for failure to get model approved.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201001_1517807327712&sectionId=2990&sectionno=32&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201001_1517807327712
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line `Whoever fails or omits to submit model of any`
  line `weight or measure for approval, shall be punished with fine which may extend to twenty thousand rupees`
  line `and for the second or subsequent offence, with imprisonment for a term which may extend to one year`
  line `and also with fine.`
obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_33:
  sectionId (2991)
  sectionNo (33)
  orderNo 33
  title `Penalty for use of unverified weight or measure.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201001_1517807327712&sectionId=2991&sectionno=33&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201001_1517807327712
obj_root_law_sections_33_content:
  string
  line `Whoever, sells, distributes, delivers or`
  line `otherwise transfers or uses any unverified weight or measure shall be punished with fine which shall not`
  line `be less than two thousand rupees but which may extend to ten thousand rupees and, for the second or`
  line `subsequent offence, with imprisonment for a term which may extend to one year and also with fine.`
obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_34:
  sectionId (2992)
  sectionNo (34)
  orderNo 34
  title `Penalty for sale or delivery of commodities. etc., by non-standard weight or measure.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_34_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 18 of 2023, s. 2 and the Schedule for certain words (w.e.f. 1-10-2023)`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201001_1517807327712&sectionId=2992&sectionno=34&orderno=34&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201001_1517807327712
obj_root_law_sections_34_content:
  string
  line `Whoever sells, or causes to be sold, delivers, or causes to be delivered, any commodity, article or thing by`
  line `any means other than the standard weight or measure or number, shall be punished with ^1[fine which may`
  line `extend to twenty-five thousand rupees and for the second offence with fine which may extend to fifty`
  line `thousand rupees and for the third and subsequent offence, with fine which may extend to one lakh`
  line rupees].
obj_root_law_sections_35:
  sectionId (2993)
  sectionNo (35)
  orderNo 35
  title `Penalty for rendering services by non-standard weight, measure or number.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_35_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201001_1517807327712&sectionId=2993&sectionno=35&orderno=35&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201001_1517807327712
obj_root_law_sections_35_content:
  string
  line Whoever
  line `renders or causes to be rendered, any service through means other than the weight or measure or`
  line `numeration or in terms of any weight, measure or number other than the standard weight or measure, shall`
  line `be punished with fine which shall not be less than two thousand rupees but which may extend to five`
  line `thousand rupees and for the second or subsequent offence, with imprisonment for a term which shall not`
  line `be less than three months but which may extend to one year, or with fine, or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_35_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_36:
  sectionId (2994)
  sectionNo (36)
  orderNo 36
  title `Penalty for selling, etc., of non-standard packages.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201001_1517807327712&sectionId=2994&sectionno=36&orderno=36&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201001_1517807327712
obj_root_law_sections_36_content:
  string
  line `(1) Whoever manufactures, packs,`
  line `imports, sells, distributes, delivers or otherwise transfers, offers, exposes or possesses for sale, or causes`
  line `to be sold, distributed, delivered or otherwise transferred, offered, exposed for sale any pre-packaged`
  line `commodity which does not conform to the declarations on the package as provided in this Act, shall be`
  line `punished with fine which may extend to twenty-five thousand rupees, for the second offence, with fine`
  line `which may extend to fifty thousand rupees and for the subsequent offence, with fine which shall not be`
  line `less than fifty thousand rupees but which may extend to one lakh rupees or with imprisonment for a term`
  line `which may extend to one year or with both.`
  line
  line `(2) Whoever manufactures or packs or imports or causes to be manufactured or packed or imported,`
  line `any pre-packaged commodity, with error in net quantity as may be prescribed shall be punished with fine`
  line `which shall not be less than ten thousand rupees but which may extend to fifty thousand rupees and for`
  line `the second and subsequent offence, with fine which may extend to one lakh rupees or with imprisonment`
  line `for a term which may extend to one year or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_37:
  sectionId (2995)
  sectionNo (37)
  orderNo 37
  title `Penalty for contravention by Government approved Test Centre.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_37_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201001_1517807327712&sectionId=2995&sectionno=37&orderno=37&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201001_1517807327712
obj_root_law_sections_37_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where any`
  line `Government approved Test Centre contravenes any of the provisions of this Act or the rules made`
  line `thereunder, or the conditions of the licence, it shall be punished with fine which may extend to one lakh`
  line rupees.
  line
  line `(2) Where any owner or employee of a Government Approved Test Centre performing duties in`
  line `accordance with the provisions of this Act or the rules made thereunder, wilfully verifies or stamps any`
  line `weight or measure in contravention of the provisions of this Act or the rules made thereunder, he shall, for`
  line `every such contravention, be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to one year or`
  line `with fine which may extend to ten thousand rupees or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_38:
  sectionId (2996)
  sectionNo (38)
  orderNo 38
  title `Penalty for non-registration by importer of weight or measure.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_38_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201001_1517807327712&sectionId=2996&sectionno=38&orderno=38&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201001_1517807327712
obj_root_law_sections_38_content:
  string
  line `Whoever imports any`
  line `weight or measure without being registered under this Act shall be punished with fine which may extend`
  line `to twenty-five thousand rupees and for the second or subsequent offence, with imprisonment for a term`
  line `which may extend to six months, or with fine, or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_38_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_39:
  sectionId (2997)
  sectionNo (39)
  orderNo 39
  title `Penalty for import of non-standard weight or measure.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_39_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201001_1517807327712&sectionId=2997&sectionno=39&orderno=39&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201001_1517807327712
obj_root_law_sections_39_content:
  string
  line `Whoever imports any non-standard`
  line `weight or measure shall be punished with fine, which may extend to fifty thousand rupees and for the`
  line `second or subsequent offence, with imprisonment for a term which may extend to one year and also with`
  line fine.
obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_40:
  sectionId (2998)
  sectionNo (40)
  orderNo 40
  title `Penalty for obstructing Director, Controller or legal metrology officer.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_40_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201001_1517807327712&sectionId=2998&sectionno=40&orderno=40&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201001_1517807327712
obj_root_law_sections_40_content:
  string
  line `Whoever obstructs`
  line `the Director, the Controller or any legal metrology officer with intent to prevent or deter the Director or`
  line `the Controller or any legal metrology officer from exercising his powers or discharging his functions, or`
  line `in consequence of anything done or attempted to be done by the Director or the Controller or any legal`
  line `metrology officer in the lawful exercise of his powers or discharge of his functions as such, or whoever`
  line `obstructs the entry of the Director or the Controller or any legal metrology officer into any premises for`
  line `inspection and verification of any weight or measure or any document or record relating thereto or the net`
  line `contents of any packaged commodity or for any other purpose shall be punished with imprisonment for a`
  line `term which may extend to two years and for the second or subsequent offence, with imprisonment for a`
  line `term which may extend to five years.`
obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_41:
  sectionId (2999)
  sectionNo (41)
  orderNo 41
  title `Penalty for giving false information or false return.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_41_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201001_1517807327712&sectionId=2999&sectionno=41&orderno=41&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201001_1517807327712
obj_root_law_sections_41_content:
  string
  line `(1) Whoever gives any information to`
  line `the Director, the Controller or any legal metrology officer, which he may require or ask for in the course`
  line `of his duty, and which such person either knows or has reason to believe to be false, shall be punished`
  line `with fine which may extend to five thousand rupees and for the second or subsequent offence with`
  line `imprisonment for a term which may extend to six months and also with fine.`
  line
  line `(2) Whoever, being required by or under this Act so to do, submits a return or maintains any record or`
  line `register which is false in material particulars, shall be punished with fine which may extend to five`
  line `thousand rupees and for the second or subsequent offence, with imprisonment for a term which may`
  line `extend to one year and also with fine.`
obj_root_law_sections_41_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_42:
  sectionId (3000)
  sectionNo (42)
  orderNo 42
  title `Vexatious search.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_42_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201001_1517807327712&sectionId=3000&sectionno=42&orderno=42&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201001_1517807327712
obj_root_law_sections_42_content:
  string
  line `The Director, the Controller or any legal metrology officer, exercising`
  line `powers under this Act or any rule made thereunder, who knows that there are no reasonable grounds for`
  line `so doing, and yet--`
  line
  line `(a) searches, or causes to be searched, any house, conveyance or place; or`
  line
  line `(b) searches any person; or`
  line
  line `(c) seizes any weight, measure or other movable property;`
  line
  line `shall, for every such offence, be punished with imprisonment for a term which may extend to one year, or`
  line `with fine which may extend to ten thousand rupees or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_43:
  sectionId (3001)
  sectionNo (43)
  orderNo 43
  title `Penalty for verification in contravention of Act and rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_43_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201001_1517807327712&sectionId=3001&sectionno=43&orderno=43&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201001_1517807327712
obj_root_law_sections_43_content:
  string
  line `Where the Controller or any legal`
  line `metrology officer exercising powers under this Act or any rule made thereunder, wilfully verifies or`
  line `stamps any weight or measure, in contravention of the provisions of this Act or of any rule made`
  line `thereunder, he shall, for every such offence, be punished with imprisonment for a term which may extend`
  line `to one year, or with fine which may extend to ten thousand rupees or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_43_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_44:
  sectionId (3002)
  sectionNo (44)
  orderNo 44
  title `Penalty for counterfeiting of seals, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_44_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201001_1517807327712&sectionId=3002&sectionno=44&orderno=44&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201001_1517807327712
obj_root_law_sections_44_content:
  string
  line `(1) Whoever--`
  line
  line `(i) counterfeits any seal specified by or under this Act or the rules made thereunder, or`
  line
  line `(ii) sells or otherwise disposes of any counterfeit seal, or`
  line
  line `(iii) possesses any counterfeit seal, or`
  line
  line `(iv) counterfeits or removes or tampers with any stamp, specified by or under this Act or rules`
  line `made thereunder, or`
  line
  line `(v) affixes the stamp so removed on, or inserts the same into, any other weight or measure,`
  line
  line `shall be punished with imprisonment for a term which shall not be less than six months but which may`
  line `extend to one year and for the second or subsequent offence, with imprisonment for a term which shall`
  line `not be less than six months but which may extend to five years.`
  line
  line `Explanation. - In this sub-section, "counterfeit" shall have the meaning assigned to it in section 28 of`
  line `the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860).`
  line
  line `(2) Whoever obtains, by unlawful means, any seal specified by or under this Act or the rules made`
  line `thereunder and uses, or causes to be used, any such seal for making any stamp on any weight or measure`
  line `with a view to representing that the stamp made by such seal is authorised by or under this Act or the`
  line `rules made thereunder shall be punished with imprisonment for a term which shall not be less than six`
  line `months but which may extend to one year and for the second or subsequent offence, with imprisonment`
  line `for a term which shall not be less than six months but which may extend to five years.`
  line
  line `(3) Whoever, being in lawful possession of a seal specified by or under this Act or the rules made`
  line `thereunder, uses, or causes to be used, such seal without any lawful authority for such use, shall be`
  line `punished with imprisonment for a term which shall not be less than six months but which may extend to`
  line `one year and for the second or subsequent offence, with imprisonment for a term which shall not be less`
  line `than six months but which may extend to five years.`
  line
  line `(4) Whoever sells or offers or exposes for sale or otherwise disposes of any weight or measure which,`
  line `he knows or has reason to believe, bears thereon a counterfeit stamp, shall be punished with imprisonment`
  line `for a term which shall not be less than six months but which may extend to one year and for the second or`
  line `subsequent offence, with imprisonment for a term which shall not be less than six months but which may`
  line `extend to five years.`
obj_root_law_sections_44_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_45:
  sectionId (3003)
  sectionNo (45)
  orderNo 45
  title `Penalty for manufacture of weight and measure without licence.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_45_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201001_1517807327712&sectionId=3003&sectionno=45&orderno=45&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201001_1517807327712
obj_root_law_sections_45_content:
  string
  line `Whoever, being required to`
  line `obtain a licence under this Act or the rules made thereunder, manufactures, without being in possession of`
  line `a valid licence, any weight or measure, shall be punished with fine which may extend to twenty thousand`
  line `rupees and for the second or subsequent offence, with imprisonment for a term which may extend to one`
  line `year, or with fine, or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_45_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_46:
  sectionId (3004)
  sectionNo (46)
  orderNo 46
  title `Penalty for repair, sale, etc., of weight and measure without licence.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_46_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201001_1517807327712&sectionId=3004&sectionno=46&orderno=46&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201001_1517807327712
obj_root_law_sections_46_content:
  string
  line `Whoever, being`
  line `required to obtain a licence under this Act or the rules made thereunder repairs or sells or offers, exposes`
  line `or possesses for repair or sale, any weight or measure, without being in possession of a valid licence, shall`
  line `be punished with fine which may extend to five thousand rupees and for the second or subsequent`
  line `offence, with imprisonment for a term which may extend to one year, or with fine, or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_47:
  sectionId (3005)
  sectionNo (47)
  orderNo 47
  title `Penalty for tampering with licence.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_47_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201001_1517807327712&sectionId=3005&sectionno=47&orderno=47&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201001_1517807327712
obj_root_law_sections_47_content:
  string
  line `Whoever alters or otherwise tampers, with any licence`
  line `issued or renewed under this Act or rules made thereunder, otherwise than in accordance with any`
  line `authorisation made by the Controller in this behalf, shall be punished with fine which may extend to`
  line `twenty thousand rupees, or with imprisonment for a term which may extend to one year or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_48:
  sectionId (3006)
  sectionNo (48)
  orderNo 48
  title `Compounding of offences.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_48_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_48_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201001_1517807327712&sectionId=3006&sectionno=48&orderno=48&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201001_1517807327712
obj_root_law_sections_48_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any offence punishable under section 25, ^1[sections 27 to 39,`
  line `section 41], sections 45 to 47, or any rule made under sub-section (3) of section 52 may, either before or`
  line `after the institution of the prosecution, be compounded, on payment for credit to the Government of such`
  line `sum as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) The Director or legal metrology officer as may be specially authorised by him in this behalf, may`
  line `compound offences punishable under section 25, ^1[sections 27 to 39, section 41], or any rule made under`
  line `sub-section (3) of section 52.`
  line
  line `(3) The Controller or legal metrology officer specially authorised by him, may compound offences`
  line `punishable under section 25, sections 27 to 31, sections 33 to 37, ^2[section 41,] sections 45 to 47, and any`
  line `rule made under sub-section (3) of section 52:`
  line
  line `Provided that such sum shall not, in any case, exceed the maximum amount of the fine, which may be`
  line `imposed under this Act for the offence so compounded.`
  line
  line `(4) Nothing in sub-section (1) shall apply to person who commits the same or similar offence, within`
  line `a period of three years from the date on which the first offence, committed by him, was compounded.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this sub-section, any second or subsequent offence committed`
  line `after the expiry of a period of three years from the date on which the offence was previously`
  line `compounded, shall be deemed to be a first offence.`
  line
  line `(5) Where an offence has been compounded under sub-section (1), no proceeding or further`
  line `proceeding, as the case may be, shall be taken against the offender in respect of the offence so`
  line compounded.
obj_root_law_sections_48_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 18 of 2023, s. 2 and the schedule for "sections 27 to 39" (w.e.f. 1-10-2023).`
  line `2. Ins. by s. 2 and the schedule, ibid, (w.e.f. 1-10-2023).`
obj_root_law_sections_49:
  sectionId (3007)
  sectionNo (49)
  orderNo 49
  title `Offences by companies and power of court to publish name, place of business, etc., for companies convicted.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_49_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201001_1517807327712&sectionId=3007&sectionno=49&orderno=49&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201001_1517807327712
obj_root_law_sections_49_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where an offence under this Act has been committed by a company,--`
  line
  line `(a) (i) the person, if any, who has been nominated under sub-section (2) to be in charge of, and`
  line `responsible to, the company for the conduct of the business of the company (hereinafter in this section`
  line `referred to as a person responsible); or`
  line
  line `(ii) where no person has been nominated, every person who at the time the offence was`
  line `committed was in charge of, and was responsible to, the company for the conduct of the business of`
  line `the company; and`
  line
  line `(b) the company,`
  line
  line `shall be deemed to be guilty of the offence and shall be liable to be proceeded against and punished`
  line `accordingly:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this sub-section shall render any such person liable to any`
  line `punishment provided in this Act if he proves that the offence was committed without his knowledge and`
  line `that he exercised all due diligence to prevent the commission of such offence.`
  line
  line `(2) Any company may, by order in writing, authorise any of its directors to exercise all such powers`
  line `and take all such steps as may be necessary or expedient to prevent the commission by the company of`
  line `any offence under this Act and may give notice to the Director or the concerned Controller or any legal`
  line `metrology officer authorised in this behalf by such Controller (hereinafter in this section referred to as the`
  line `authorised officer) in such form and in such manner as may be prescribed, that it has nominated such`
  line `director as the person responsible, along with the written consent of such director for being so nominated.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--Where a company has different establishments or branches or different units in any`
  line `establishment or branch, different persons may be nominated under this sub-section in relation to different`
  line `establishments or branches or units and the person nominated in relation to any establishment, branch or`
  line `unit shall be deemed to be the person responsible in respect of such establishment, branch or unit.`
  line
  line `(3) The person nominated under sub-section (2) shall, until--`
  line
  line `(i) further notice cancelling such nomination is received from the company by the Director or the`
  line `concerned Controller or the authorised officer; or`
  line
  line `(ii) he ceases to be a director of the company; or`
  line
  line `(iii) he makes a request in writing to the Director or the concerned Controller or the legal`
  line `metrology officer under intimation to the company, to cancel the nomination, which request shall be`
  line `complied with by the Director or the concerned Controller or the legal metrology officer,`
  line
  line `whichever is the earliest, continue to be the person responsible:`
  line
  line `Provided that where such person ceases to be a director of the company, he shall intimate the fact of`
  line `such cessation to the Director or the concerned Controller or the authorised officer:`
  line
  line `Provided further that where such person makes a request under clause (iii) the Director or the`
  line `concerned Controller or the authorised officer shall not cancel such nomination with effect from a date`
  line `earlier than the date on which the request is made.`
  line
  line `(4) Notwithstanding anything contained in the foregoing sub-sections, where an offence under this`
  line `Act has been committed by a company and it is proved that the offence has been committed with the`
  line `consent or connivance of, or is attributable to the neglect on the part of, any director, manager, secretary`
  line `or other officer, not being a person nominated under sub-section (2), such director, manager, secretary or`
  line `other officer shall also be deemed to be guilty of that offence and shall be liable to be proceeded against`
  line `and punished accordingly.`
  line
  line `(5) Where any company is convicted under this Act for contravention of any of the provisions thereof,`
  line `it shall be competent for the court convicting the company to cause the name and place of business of the`
  line `company, nature of the contravention, the fact that the company has been so convicted and such other`
  line `particulars as the court may consider to be appropriate in the circumstances of the case, to be published at`
  line `the expense of the company in such newspaper or in such other manner as the court may direct.`
  line
  line `(6) No publication under sub-section (5) shall be made until the period for preferring an appeal`
  line `against the orders of the court has expired without any appeal having been preferred, or such an appeal,`
  line `having been preferred, has been disposed of.`
  line
  line `(7) The expenses of any publication under sub-section (5) shall be recoverable from the company as if`
  line `it were a fine imposed by the court.`
  line
  line `"Explanation".--For the purposes of this section,--`
  line
  line `(a) "company" means any body corporate and includes a firm or other association of individuals;`
  line and
  line
  line `(b) "director", in relation to a firm, means a partner in the firm but excludes nominated directors,`
  line `honorary directors, Government nominated directors.`
obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_50:
  sectionId (3008)
  sectionNo (50)
  orderNo 50
  title Appeals.
  content obj_root_law_sections_50_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_50_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201001_1517807327712&sectionId=3008&sectionno=50&orderno=50&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201001_1517807327712
obj_root_law_sections_50_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the provisions of sub-section (2), an appeal shall lie,--`
  line
  line `(a) from every decision or order under sections 15 to 20, section 22, section 25, sections 27 to 39,`
  line `section 41 or any rule made under sub-section (3) of section 52 by the legal metrology officer`
  line `appointed under section 13, to the Director;`
  line
  line `(b) from every decision or order made by the Director of Legal Metrology under sections 15 to 20, section 22, section 25, sections 27 to 39, section 41 or any rule made under sub-section (3) of section 52, to the Central Government or any officer specially authorised in this behalf by that`
  line Government;
  line
  line `(c) from every decision given by the Controller of Legal Metrology under delegated powers of`
  line `Director Legal Metrology to the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(d) from every decision given or order made under sections 15 to 18, sections 23 to 25, sections`
  line `27 to 37, sections 45 to 47 or any rule made under sub-section (3) of section 53 by any legal`
  line `metrology officer appointed under section 14, to the Controller; and`
  line
  line `(e) from every decision given or order made by the Controller under sections 15 to 18, sections 23`
  line `to 25, sections 27 to 37, sections 45 to 47 or any rule made under sub-section (3) of section 53 not`
  line `being an order made in appeal under clause (d), to the State Government or any officer specially`
  line `authorised in this behalf by that Government.`
  line
  line `(2) Every such appeal shall be preferred within sixty days from the date on which the impugned order`
  line `was made:`
  line
  line `Provided that the appellate authority may, if it is satisfied that the appellant was prevented by`
  line `sufficient cause from preferring the appeal within the said period of sixty days, permit the appellant to`
  line `prefer the appeal within a further period of sixty days.`
  line
  line `(3) On receipt of any such appeal, the appellate authority shall, after giving the parties to the appeal, a`
  line `reasonable opportunity of being heard and after making such inquiry as it deems proper, make such order,`
  line `as it may think fit, confirming, modifying or reversing the decision or order appealed against or may send`
  line `back the case with such direction as it may think fit for a fresh decision or order after taking additional`
  line `evidence, if necessary.`
  line
  line `(4) Every appeal shall be preferred on payment of such fees, as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(5) The Central Government or the State Government, as the case may be, may on its own motion or`
  line `otherwise, call for and examine the record of any proceeding including a proceeding in appeal in which`
  line `any decision or order has been made, for the purpose of satisfying itself as to the correctness, legality or`
  line `propriety of such decision or order and may pass such orders thereon as it may think fit:`
  line
  line `Provided that no decision or order shall be varied under this sub-section so as to prejudicially affect`
  line `any person unless such person has been given a reasonable opportunity of showing cause against the`
  line `proposed action.`
obj_root_law_sections_50_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_51:
  sectionId (3009)
  sectionNo (51)
  orderNo 51
  title `Provisions of Indian Penal Code and Code of Criminal Procedure not to apply.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_51_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_51_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201001_1517807327712&sectionId=3009&sectionno=51&orderno=51&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201001_1517807327712
obj_root_law_sections_51_content:
  string
  line The
  line `provisions of the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860) and section 153 of the Code of Criminal Procedure,`
  line `1973 (2 of 1974) in so far as such provisions relate to offences with regard to weight or measure, shall not`
  line `apply to any offence which is punishable under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_51_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_52:
  sectionId (3010)
  sectionNo (52)
  orderNo 52
  title `Power of the Central Government to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_52_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_52_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201001_1517807327712&sectionId=3010&sectionno=52&orderno=52&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201001_1517807327712
obj_root_law_sections_52_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by`
  line `notification, make rules for carrying out the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the specification of the base units of measures and base unit of mass under sub-section (2) of`
  line `section 5;`
  line
  line `(b) the manner of preparation of objects and equipments under sub-section (3) of section 7;`
  line
  line `(c) physical characteristics, configuration, constructional details, materials, equipment,`
  line `performance, tolerances, period of re-verification, methods or procedures of tests under`
  line `sub-section (4) of section 7;`
  line
  line `(d) reference standards, secondary standards and working standards of weights and measures`
  line `under sub-section (1) of section 9;`
  line
  line `(e) reference standards, secondary standards and working standards shall be verified and stamped`
  line `and the fee under sub-section (2) of section 9;`
  line
  line `(f) the weight or measure or number in which any transaction, dealing, or contract in respect of`
  line `any goods, class of goods or undertakings shall be made under section 10;`
  line
  line `(g) the qualifications of the Director and legal metrology officers under sub-section (2) of`
  line `section 13;`
  line
  line `(h) the qualification of the Controller and legal metrology officers under sub-section (2) of`
  line `section 14;`
  line
  line `(i) the manner of disposal of goods under sub-section (3) of section 15;`
  line
  line `(j) the standard quantities or number and the manner in which the packages shall bear the`
  line `declarations and the particulars under sub-section (1) of section 18;`
  line
  line `(k) the manner and registration and the fee under section 19;`
  line
  line `(l) the management and control of the Institute, the teaching staff and other employees, the`
  line `courses and curricula for training thereat, the qualifications, which a person shall possess in order to`
  line `be eligible for admission thereto under sub-section (2) of section 21;`
  line
  line `(m) the manner, fee and authority for approval of models under section 22;`
  line
  line `(n) the kinds of weights or measures under sub-section (2) of section 24;`
  line
  line `(o) the manner in which, terms and conditions on which and fee on payment which the Central`
  line `Government shall notify the Government approved Test Centre under sub-section (3) of section 24;`
  line
  line `(p) the qualifications and experience of persons appointed or engaged and the fee and terms and`
  line `conditions on which Government approved Test Centre shall verify the weight or measure under`
  line `sub-section (4) of section 24;`
  line
  line `(q) the error in net quantity under sub-section (2) of section 36;`
  line
  line `(r) fee for compounding of offence under sub-section (1) of section 48;`
  line
  line `(s) form and manner in which notice to the Director or the Controller or any other officer`
  line `authorised by him shall be given under sub-section (2) of section 49.`
  line
  line `(3) In making any rule under this section, the Central Government may provide that a breach thereof`
  line `shall be punishable with fine which may extend to five thousand rupees.`
  line
  line `(4) Every rule made by the Central Government under this Act shall be laid, as soon as may be after it`
  line `is made, before each House of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days which`
  line `may be comprised in one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the`
  line `session immediately following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in`
  line `making any modification in the rule or both Houses agree that the rule should not be made, the rule shall`
  line `thereafter have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that any such modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done`
  line `under that rule.`
obj_root_law_sections_52_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_53:
  sectionId (3011)
  sectionNo (53)
  orderNo 53
  title `Power of State Government to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_53_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_53_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201001_1517807327712&sectionId=3011&sectionno=53&orderno=53&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201001_1517807327712
obj_root_law_sections_53_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State Government may, by notification,`
  line `and after consultation with the Central Government, make rules to carry out the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the time within which the weight or measure may be got verified under proviso to`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 16;`
  line
  line `(b) registers and records to be maintained by persons referred to under sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 17;`
  line
  line `(c) the form, manner, conditions, period, area of jurisdiction and fees for issuance of licence`
  line `under sub-section (2) of section 23;`
  line
  line `(d) fee for verification and stamping of any weight or measure under sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 24;`
  line
  line `(e) manner of notifying Government approved Test Centre, terms and conditions and fee to be`
  line `paid under sub-section (3) of section 24;`
  line
  line `(f) fee for compounding of offences under sub-section (1) of section 48.`
  line
  line `(3) In making any rule under this section, the State Government may provide that a breach thereof`
  line `shall be punishable with fine which may extend to five thousand rupees.`
  line
  line `(4) The power to make rules under this section shall be subject to the condition of the rules being`
  line `made after previous publication in Official Gazette.`
  line
  line `(5) Every rule made under this section shall, as soon as may be after it is made, be laid before each`
  line `House of State Legislature, where there are two Houses and where there is one House of State`
  line `Legislature, before that House.`
obj_root_law_sections_53_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_54:
  sectionId (3012)
  sectionNo (54)
  orderNo 54
  title `Delegation of Powers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_54_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_54_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201001_1517807327712&sectionId=3012&sectionno=54&orderno=54&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201001_1517807327712
obj_root_law_sections_54_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, in consultation with the State`
  line `Government and by notification, direct that any power exercisable by it under this Act or any rule made`
  line `thereunder, not being a power conferred by section 50 relating to appeal or section 52 relating to power to`
  line `make rules, in relation to such matters and subject to such conditions as may be specified, may be`
  line `exercised also by such officer subordinate to it as may be specified in the notification.`
  line
  line `(2) Subject to any general or special direction or condition imposed by the State Government, any`
  line `person authorised by the Central Government to exercise any powers may exercise those powers in the`
  line `same manner and to the same extent as if they had been conferred on that person directly by this Act and`
  line `not by way of delegation.`
obj_root_law_sections_54_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_55:
  sectionId (3013)
  sectionNo (55)
  orderNo 55
  title `Act not to apply in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_55_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_55_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201001_1517807327712&sectionId=3013&sectionno=55&orderno=55&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201001_1517807327712
obj_root_law_sections_55_content:
  string
  line `The provisions of this Act, in so far as they relate to`
  line `verification and stamping of weights and measures, shall not apply to any weight or measure,--`
  line
  line `(a) used in any factory exclusively engaged in the manufacture of any arms, ammunition or both,`
  line `for the use of the Armed Forces of the Union;`
  line
  line `(b) used for scientific investigation or for research;`
  line
  line `(c) manufactured exclusively for export.`
obj_root_law_sections_55_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_56:
  sectionId (3014)
  sectionNo (56)
  orderNo 56
  title `Existing Director, Controller and legal metrology officer not to be affected by the new qualification to be prescribed.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_56_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_56_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201001_1517807327712&sectionId=3014&sectionno=56&orderno=56&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201001_1517807327712
obj_root_law_sections_56_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every Director, Controller and legal metrology officer appointed`
  line `immediately before the commencement of the rules made under this Act, shall be deemed to have been`
  line `appointed under sub-section (1) of sections 13 and 14, notwithstanding any rule prescribing different`
  line qualifications.
  line
  line `(2) The rules made by a State Government under the Standards of Weights and Measures`
  line `(Enforcement) Act, 1985 (54 of 1985) which are in force immediately before the commencement of this`
  line `Act shall remain in force until the State Government, makes rules in that behalf.`
obj_root_law_sections_56_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_57:
  sectionId (3015)
  sectionNo (57)
  orderNo 57
  title `Repeal of the Standards of Weights and Measures Act, 1976 and Standards of Weights and Measures (Enforcement) Act, 1985.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_57_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_57_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201001_1517807327712&sectionId=3015&sectionno=57&orderno=57&orgactid=AC_CEN_21_44_00007_201001_1517807327712
obj_root_law_sections_57_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Standards of Weights and Measures Act, 1976`
  line `(60 of 1976) and the Standards of Weights and Measures (Enforcement) Act, 1985 (54 of 1985), is hereby`
  line repealed.
  line
  line `(2) Without prejudice to the provisions contained in the General Clauses Act, 1897 (10 of 1897), with`
  line `respect to repeals, any notification, rule or order made under the Standards of Weights and Measures Act,`
  line `1976 (60 of 1976) and the Standards of Weights and Measures (Enforcement) Act, 1985 (54 of 1985),`
  line `shall, if in force, at the commencement of this Act, continue to be in force and have effect as if it was`
  line `made under the corresponding provision of this Act.`
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding such repeal, any appointment, notification, rule, order, registration, licence,`
  line `certificate, notice, decision, approval, authorisation or consent made, issued or given under such law shall,`
  line `if in force at the commencement of this Act, continue to be in force and have effect as if it were made,`
  line `issued or given under the corresponding provisions of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_57_footnotes:
  string
  line
